I believe this is caused by the HadoopFileIO [no-arg constructor](https://github.com/apache/iceberg/blob/01393a06c284175edab75de34f48b2bfbd606081/core/src/main/java/org/apache/iceberg/hadoop/HadoopFileIO.java#L42) not setting an empty conf. Using the `HadoopFileIO` directly you can use `setConf` to add an empty configuration (when reading local files) and the NPE goes away. Should the no-arg constructor do the same?

```java
  public HadoopFileIO() {
    Configuration conf = new Configuration();
    this.hadoopConf = new SerializableConfiguration(conf)::get;
  }
```

Otherwise, is there some other way to set an empty conf before `JdbcCatalog` uses it?

Hah, I made this issue too quickly. Using the `setConf` method on `JdbcCatalog` solves this (I was using the interface as the type which is why I missed it).
```java
import org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration;
...

JdbcCatalog catalog = new JdbcCatalog();
Configuration conf = new Configuration();
catalog.setConf(conf)
catalog.initialize("demo", properties);
```
